Task Tracker.Unnamed: 1: Why is order in partially shipped?
Task Tracker.Unnamed: 12:
In progress with Erica, was able to reproduce in a new order, figured out that the reason why the order was showing as Partially Shipped was due to the orderLine's pickTasks being associated with component assembly items while the orderLine maintains the parent item; currently trying to figure out how to resolve if AssignTripToContainer process is the cause
Figured out B2B Wholesale orders in this situation was displaying as Partially Shipped when pallets are getting picking separately into multiple picking containers and then taken through ATTC, each picking container would correspond to a generated Shipment --> the shipped quantity would only display as the first picking container - or pallet quantity of 432, which would correspond to a shipped quantity of 72 of the parent item; in order to account for the multiple shipments, ATTC SI BATCH_CLOSE_SHIPMENT consolidates all of the picking containers onto one shipment with each of them displaying as a ContainerHist, so they don't lose any tracking visibility

GoNo-Go Decision.Unnamed: 3: To achieve a "YES" UAT onsite recommendation

To achieve a "YES" go-live recommendation, two things must occur:
(1) all items with a weight of 10 must have a % complete of at least 90%, and 
(2) the Total Percentage score at the bottom must have a % complete of at least 90%.  
Note,  even if these conditions are met, if the score is not 100%, there could be issues when going live.
